@notice upgradeOracle allows the contract owner to update the oracle factory address
@param _newOracle is the address of the new oracle factory contract.*

v@notice upgradeMoneyMarketFactory allows the contract owner to update the Money Market factory address
@param _newMMF is the address of the new Money Market factory contract.*

@notice upgradeARTFactory allows the contract owner to update the ART Factory address
@param _ARTF is the address of the new ART factory contract.*

@notice getAsset returns an array of all assets whitelisted on the platform.
@dev this can be used to loop through and retreive each assets MoneyMarket by the front end*

@notice _checkIfALR is used to check if an input address is an ALR contract
@param __inQ is the address in question*

params._ALR: is the address of the ALR token where collateral value is being looked up*
params._borrower: is the address whos collateral value we are looking up

params._ALR: is the address of the ALR being used as collateral*
params._borrower: is the address of the borrower

params._oracle: is the address for the UniswapOracleFactorycontract*

getAssets().details: this can be used to loop through and retreive each assets MoneyMarket by the front end*

params._ALR: is the address of the Asko Low Risk token that was used as collateral*
params._borrower: is the address of the account being liquidated
params._liquidator: is the address of the account doing the liquidating

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setUpAHR(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint256.details: this function can only be called after an asset has been whitelisted as it needs an existing MoneyMarketInstance contract*

params._assetContractAdd: is the contract address of the asset whos MoneyMarketInstance is being set up
params._baseRatePerYear: The approximate target base APR, as a mantissa (scaled by 1e18)
params._fee: is a number representing the fee for exchanging an AHR token, as a mantissa (scaled by 1e18)
params._jumpMultiplierPerYear: The multiplierPerBlock after hitting a specified utilization point
params._multiplierPerYear: The rate of increase in interest rate wrt utilization (scaled by 1e18)
params._optimal: The utilization point at which the jump multiplier is applied(Refered to as the Kink in the InterestRateModel)

setUpALR(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint256.details: this function can only be called after an asset has been whitelisted as it needs an existing MoneyMarketInstance contract*

params._assetContractAdd: is the contract address of the asset whos MoneyMarketInstance is being set up
params._baseRatePerYear: The approximate target base APR, as a mantissa (scaled by 1e18)
params._fee: is a number representing the fee for exchanging an ALR token, as a mantissa (scaled by 1e18)
params._jumpMultiplierPerYear: The multiplierPerBlock after hitting a specified utilization point
params._multiplierPerYear: The rate of increase in interest rate wrt utilization (scaled by 1e18)
params._optimal: The utilization point at which the jump multiplier is applied(Refered to as the Kink in the InterestRateModel)

trackCollateralDown(address,address,uint.details: this function can only be called by a MoneyMarketInstance.*

params._ALR: is the address of the seller
params._amount: is the amount of USDC being collateralized

trackCollateralUp(address,address,uint25.details: this function can only be called by a MoneyMarketInstance.*

params._ALR: is the address of the ALR being collateralized
params._amount: is the amount of USDC being collateralized
params._borrower: is the address of the corrower

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params._assetContractAdd: is the contract address of the asset whos MoneyMarketInstance is being set up
params._baseRatePerYear: The approximate target base APR, as a mantissa (scaled by 1e18)
params._isALR: is a bool representing whether or not the Asko risk token being updated is a ALR or not*
params._jumpMultiplierPerYear: The multiplierPerBlock after hitting a specified utilization point
params._multiplierPerYear: The rate of increase in interest rate wrt utilization (scaled by 1e18)
params._optimal: The utilization point at which the jump multiplier is applied(Refered to as the Kink in the InterestRateModel)

params._asset: is the address of the asset(token) whos ART tokens are being updated*
params._isALR: is a bool representing whether of not the Reserve ratio being updated iis an ALR or not
params._newRR: is the new reserve ratio value(scaled by 1e18)

params._ARTF: is the address of the new ART factory contract.*

params._asset: is the address of the asset the MoneyMarketInstance controls*

params._newMMF: is the address of the new Money Market factory contract.*

params._newOracle: is the address of the new oracle factory contract.*

params._assetContractAdd: is the address of the ERC20 asset being whitelisted
params._assetName: is the name of the asset(e.x: ChainLink)
params._assetSymbol: is the symbol of the asset(e.x: LINK)*

_checkIfALR(address).notice: _checkIfALR is used to check if an input address is an ALR contract

checkAvailibleCollateralValue(address,ad.notice: checkCollateralValue is a view function that accepts an account address and an ALR contract address and returns the USD value of the availible collateral they have. Availible collateral is determined by the total amount of collateral minus the amount of collateral that is still availible to borrow against

checkCollateralizedALR(address,address).notice: checkCollateralizedALR is used by the front end to check a borrowers collateralized ALR amount

methods.constructor: the constructor function is fired during the contract deployment process. The constructor can only be fired once and is used to set up Oracle variables for the MoneyMarketFactory contract.

getAssets().notice: getAsset returns an array of all assets whitelisted on the platform.

liquidateTrigger(uint256,address,address.notice: liquidateTrigger is a protected function that can only be called by a money market instance.

setUpAHR(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint256.notice: setUpAHR is used to set up a MoneyMarketInstances Asko High Risk Token as well as its InterestRateModel

setUpALR(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint256.notice: setUpAHR is used to set up a MoneyMarketInstances Asko High Risk Token as well as its InterestRateModel

trackCollateralDown(address,address,uint.notice: trackCollateralDown is an external function used bya MMI to track collateral amounts globally

trackCollateralUp(address,address,uint25.notice: trackCollateralUp is an external function used bya MMI to track collateral amounts globally

updateIRM(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint25.notice: updateIRM allows the admin of this contract to update a AskoRiskToken's Interest Rate Model

updateRR(uint256,bool,address).notice: updateRR allows the admin to update the reserve ratio for an Asko Risk Token

upgradeARTFactory(address).notice: upgradeARTFactory allows the contract owner to update the ART Factory address

upgradeMMIOracle(address).notice: upgradeMMIOracle allows the owner of the Money Market Control contract to update the oracle factory contract that a Money Market instance points to

upgradeMoneyMarketFactory(address).notice: upgradeMoneyMarketFactory allows the contract owner to update the Money Market factory address

upgradeOracle(address).notice: upgradeOracle allows the contract owner to update the oracle factory address

whitelistAsset(address,string,string).notice: whitelistAsset is an onlyOwner function designed to be called by the AskoDAO. This function creates a new MoneyMarketInstancecontract for an input asset as well as a UniswapOracleInstance for the asset.
